==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mushy
<hw>Mush"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Soft like mush;
figuratively, good-naturedly weak and effusive; weakly
sentimental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She 's not <qex>mushy</qex>, but her heart is tender.</q>
<rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Music</ent>⟦br⟧
